    <item>
      <title>Finding Information</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/search-sources/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/search-sources/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When you ask Lumen a question, it searches for the best available evidence before answering. You can choose &lt;strong&gt;where&lt;/strong&gt; it looks using three simple buttons at the bottom of the chat.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-three-knowledge-sources&#34;&gt;The Three Knowledge Sources&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #3B82F61a; color: #3B82F6;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#9889;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Database&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Lumen&amp;#39;s built-in clinical knowledge base. Contains peer-reviewed guidelines, drug databases, lab reference ranges, and clinical protocols. This is your primary source of truth.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What are the current USPSTF screening recommendations for lung cancer?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #3B82F61a; color: #3B82F6;&#34;&gt;On by Default&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #6633CC1a; color: #6633CC;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128193;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;My Documents&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Your personally uploaded files — PDFs, notes, research papers, and reference materials. Toggle this on when you want Lumen to search your own library.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Based on the uploaded protocol, what are the inclusion criteria for this trial?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #2999661a; color: #299966;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#127760;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Web Search&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Live internet search for the most current information. Useful for breaking research, conference proceedings, or topics not yet in the clinical database.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What were the key findings from the latest ASCO 2026 presentations on NSCLC?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-search-works&#34;&gt;How Search Works&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When you send a message with search enabled, here&amp;rsquo;s what happens:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Research &amp; Evidence</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/literature-research/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/literature-research/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Need to look something up in PubMed mid-round? Want to check what the FDA label actually says? Just ask. Lumen searches the major medical databases and brings the results right into your conversation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128218;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;PubMed Search&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Searches the PubMed/MEDLINE database via NLM E-utilities. Finds relevant articles, fetches abstracts, and ranks results by relevance to your question.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Find recent systematic reviews on SGLT2 inhibitors and heart failure outcomes&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Research&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128138;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;FDA Drug Labels&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Queries the openFDA drug labeling API. Returns official FDA-approved label information including indications, dosing, warnings, and contraindications.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What does the FDA label say about semaglutide contraindications?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;Regulatory&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129514;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Trials Search&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Searches ClinicalTrials.gov for active and completed studies. Filter by condition, recruitment status, and trial phase.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Find active Phase 3 trials for NASH/MASH treatment&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Research&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-pubmed-search-works&#34;&gt;How PubMed Search Works&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When Lumen searches PubMed, you&amp;rsquo;ll see a tool call block showing the progress:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Medication Questions</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/medications/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/medications/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;These are the questions that come up a dozen times a shift. &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Can I give these two together?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;What&amp;rsquo;s the drip rate?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Does this need a dose adjustment for their kidneys?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; Just type the question and Lumen handles the rest.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128138;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Drug Name Lookup (RxNorm)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Resolves drug names via NLM RxNorm. Works with brand names, generics, abbreviations, and even misspellings. Returns the normalized name, RxCUI, ingredients, and drug class.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Look up the generic name for Jardiance&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;Lookup&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#9888;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Drug Interactions&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Checks drug-drug interactions using the FDA interaction database. Returns severity level, mechanism of interaction, and clinical management recommendations.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Check interactions between warfarin, amiodarone, and metoprolol&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;Safety&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128167;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;IV Drip Calculator&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Calculates IV infusion rates from weight-based dosing. Computes mL/hr with titration guidance. Supports common drips like vasopressors, insulin, and heparin.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Calculate norepinephrine drip at 0.1 mcg/kg/min for an 80kg patient&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Calculator&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129656;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Renal Dose Adjustment&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Computes creatinine clearance (Cockcroft-Gault), determines CKD stage, and looks up FDA-recommended dose adjustments for renal impairment.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Renal dose check for vancomycin in a 70-year-old male, 85kg, SCr 2.1&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Calculator&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128200;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;FDA Adverse Events&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Searches the FDA FAERS (adverse event reporting) database. Aggregates reaction reports by drug, showing frequencies, outcomes, and severity distributions.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What are the most reported adverse events for methotrexate?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;Safety&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128680;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;FDA Drug Recalls&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Checks the FDA enforcement and recall database. Shows recall classifications, affected lots, and current status.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Are there any recent recalls for metformin products?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;Safety&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;drug-interaction-example&#34;&gt;Drug Interaction Example&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s what a drug interaction check looks like in action:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Codes, Labs &amp; Calculators</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/coding-labs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/coding-labs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Nobody went to medical school to memorize billing codes. Describe the diagnosis or procedure in your own words and Lumen finds the right code. It also checks lab reference ranges, verifies Medicare coverage, and runs clinical calculators like CHA₂DS₂-VASc and MELD.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#127973;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;ICD-10 Lookup&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Search ICD-10-CM diagnostic codes. Matches clinical descriptions to specific codes with laterality, severity, and sequencing guidance.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ICD-10 code for acute anterolateral STEMI, initial encounter&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Coding&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129534;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;CPT Lookup&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Find CPT procedure codes. Resolves procedure descriptions to billing codes with intensity levels and component breakdowns.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;CPT code for laparoscopic cholecystectomy&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;Coding&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128203;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;HCPCS Lookup&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Search HCPCS Level II codes for DME, supplies, and non-physician services. Covers J-codes for drugs, E-codes for equipment, and more.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;HCPCS code for a standard wheelchair&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Coding&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#9989;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;CMS Coverage Lookup&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Check Medicare coverage determinations — both National (NCDs) and Local (LCDs). Returns coverage criteria and required documentation.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Does Medicare cover continuous glucose monitoring for type 2 diabetes?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;Insurance&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129514;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Lab Reference Ranges&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;LOINC-mapped laboratory reference ranges. Returns normal intervals adjusted for units, age, and sex, with clinical significance notes for abnormal values.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What is the normal reference range for TSH?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;Labs&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129518;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Medical Calculator&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Validated clinical scoring tools — eGFR, CHA₂DS₂-VASc, MELD, CURB-65, Wells criteria, APACHE II, and more. Returns scores with interpretation.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Calculate MELD-Na score: bilirubin 3.2, INR 1.8, creatinine 1.5, sodium 131&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;Calculator&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;icd-10-code-search-in-action&#34;&gt;ICD-10 Code Search in Action&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup&#34; style=&#34;margin: 2rem 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-avatar&#34;&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-title&#34;&gt;Chat&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg user&#34;&gt;ICD-10 code for type 2 diabetes with diabetic chronic kidney disease stage 3&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg assistant&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-avatar&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool&#34;&gt;&#xA;          &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;span class=&#34;mock-tool-status done&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            Looked up ICD-10 codes&#xA;          &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;          &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool-detail&#34;&gt;query: &#34;type 2 diabetes diabetic chronic kidney disease stage 3&#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;p style=&#34;margin:0; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-on-dark);&#34;&gt;&#xA;          For T2DM with diabetic CKD stage 3, you&#39;ll need two codes:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;          &lt;strong&gt;E11.22&lt;/strong&gt; — Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic chronic kidney disease&lt;br&gt;&#xA;          &lt;strong&gt;N18.3&lt;/strong&gt; — Chronic kidney disease, stage 3 (unspecified)&#xA;        &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Protocols &amp; Decision Support</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/protocols-decisions/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/protocols-decisions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When you need to work through a clinical problem systematically — building a differential, choosing an antibiotic, following a protocol — Lumen does the structured work so you can focus on the patient.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#9745;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Checklists&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Evidence-based protocol checklists for sepsis bundles, DKA management, central line insertion, surgical safety, and more. Interactive — track completion by checking items.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Give me a sepsis 3-hour bundle checklist&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;Protocols&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #ED89361a; color: #ED8936;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#127973;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Triage Scoring&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Emergency triage systems — ESI (Emergency Severity Index), MTS (Manchester Triage), CTAS, and START. Scores patient acuity from clinical presentation.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Triage a 55-year-old with chest pain, diaphoresis, and BP 90/60&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #ED89361a; color: #ED8936;&#34;&gt;Emergency&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129504;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Differential Diagnosis&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Generates a ranked differential diagnosis based on symptoms, demographics, vitals, and history. Searches PubMed and maps to ICD-10. Includes distinguishing features and recommended workup.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Differential for a 30-year-old with acute onset pleuritic chest pain and dyspnea&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Diagnosis&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#129440;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Antimicrobial Selector&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Selects appropriate antibiotic therapy based on IDSA guidelines. Considers infection type, severity, allergies, and pregnancy status. Returns first/second-line regimens with dosing and duration.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Best antibiotic for community-acquired pneumonia, PCN allergy, outpatient&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #34C7591a; color: #34C759;&#34;&gt;Treatment&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128165;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Allergy Cross-Reactivity&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Identifies cross-reactive drugs and safe alternatives for patients with known drug allergies. Maps allergy patterns and suggests de-sensitization options.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;What can I use instead of cephalexin if the patient has a penicillin allergy?&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;Safety&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128214;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Guidelines&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Searches USPSTF and PubMed for practice guidelines (2020&amp;#43;). Returns recommendations with letter grades and evidence summaries.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Current guidelines for managing newly diagnosed hypertension&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Guidelines&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128077;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Recommendations&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Generates prioritized, evidence-graded recommendations (Grade A through D). Context-specific with supporting rationale.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Recommendations for secondary stroke prevention in a patient with PFO&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Evidence&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128179;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;NPI Lookup&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Searches the NPI provider registry. Resolves provider name, specialty, taxonomy, and practice location. Useful for referrals and verification.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Look up cardiologists in Austin, TX&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;Directory&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;differential-diagnosis-in-action&#34;&gt;Differential Diagnosis in Action&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The differential diagnosis tool is one of Lumen&amp;rsquo;s most powerful clinical features:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Patient Records &amp; Notes</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/patient-records/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/patient-records/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If your practice has EHR integration set up, Lumen can pull a patient&amp;rsquo;s current medications, recent labs, and diagnoses right into the conversation. It can also draft clinical notes and check scheduling availability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;callout callout-warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;callout-icon&#34;&gt;&amp;#9888;&amp;#65039;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EHR integration requires setup.&lt;/strong&gt; These tools are only available after configuring your FHIR connection in Settings &amp;gt; EHR Integration. See your administrator for access.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128100;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;FHIR Patient Data&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Queries your EHR via FHIR R4. Pulls current medications, recent labs, active diagnoses, allergies, and encounter history for a specific patient.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Pull the current medication list for patient ID 12345&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #3DBF801a; color: #3DBF80;&#34;&gt;EHR&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128197;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Scheduling&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Queries the booking system for available appointment slots. Filter by provider, specialty, date range, and location.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Show available cardiology slots next week&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;EHR&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128221;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Notes&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Auto-generates clinical documentation — SOAP notes, H&amp;amp;P notes, discharge summaries, and referral letters. Structured according to standard clinical formats.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Generate a SOAP note for today&amp;#39;s visit — 45yo with uncontrolled HTN&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Documentation&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;clinical-note-generation&#34;&gt;Clinical Note Generation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Lumen can draft several types of clinical documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Creating Documents</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/document-generation/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/document-generation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Need slides for grand rounds by tomorrow? A patient education handout? A spreadsheet tracking your department&amp;rsquo;s metrics? Just tell Lumen what you need, and it creates a professional, ready-to-edit document you can download right away.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128196;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;PDF Creation&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Generates formatted PDF documents — patient summaries, protocol references, research summaries, and more. Download directly from the artifact panel.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Create a PDF summary of our discussion about this patient&amp;#39;s treatment plan&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #E53E3E1a; color: #E53E3E;&#34;&gt;Documents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #D69E2E1a; color: #D69E2E;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128202;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Presentations (PPTX)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Builds PowerPoint slide decks with professional formatting. Great for grand rounds, patient education, and team presentations.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Create a 10-slide presentation on the latest sepsis management guidelines for our grand rounds&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #D69E2E1a; color: #D69E2E;&#34;&gt;Documents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #2173461a; color: #217346;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128203;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Spreadsheets (Excel)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Generates Excel workbooks with formatted data tables, calculations, and organized sheets. Useful for tracking, reporting, and data organization.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Create a spreadsheet tracking our department&amp;#39;s antibiotic stewardship metrics&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #2173461a; color: #217346;&#34;&gt;Documents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#127760;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Interactive HTML&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Creates self-contained interactive HTML documents — calculators, decision trees, patient education materials with interactive elements.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Build an interactive patient education page about diabetes self-management&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #0EA5E91a; color: #0EA5E9;&#34;&gt;Interactive&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#127891;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;CME Quiz&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Generates board-style multiple-choice questions with detailed rationales. Perfect for self-study, teaching, and exam preparation.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Create a 5-question quiz on atrial fibrillation management&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Education&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;presentation-example&#34;&gt;Presentation Example&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup&#34; style=&#34;margin: 2rem 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-avatar&#34;&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-title&#34;&gt;Chat&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg user&#34;&gt;Create a presentation on COPD management guidelines for our nursing staff education session&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg assistant&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-avatar&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool&#34;&gt;&#xA;          &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;span class=&#34;mock-tool-status done&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            Created presentation&#xA;          &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;          &lt;div class=&#34;mock-tool-detail&#34;&gt;title: &#34;COPD Management Guidelines&#34; &amp;middot; 8 slides&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;p style=&#34;margin:0; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-on-dark);&#34;&gt;&#xA;          I&#39;ve created an 8-slide presentation covering GOLD guidelines, pharmacotherapy stepwise approach, and acute exacerbation management.&#xA;        &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Privacy &amp; Safety</title>
      <link>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/privacy/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docs.lumenai.health/tools/privacy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Need to share a clinical note with a colleague but want to strip the patient&amp;rsquo;s name and MRN first? Lumen can de-identify text automatically. It also has a safe email tool for sending prior auth letters and other correspondence.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;available-tools&#34;&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128274;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;De-identify PHI&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Automatically removes protected health information from text — names, dates, MRNs, addresses, and other identifiers. Replaces them with consistent pseudonyms so the text remains readable.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;De-identify this clinical note before I share it with the research team&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #5865F21a; color: #5865F2;&#34;&gt;Privacy&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128275;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Re-identify PHI&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Restores original PHI from de-identified text using the session mapping. Only works within the same session where de-identification occurred.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Re-identify the note from earlier&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #8C66D91a; color: #8C66D9;&#34;&gt;Privacy&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tool-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &amp;#128231;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tool-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-name&#34;&gt;Send Email&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-desc&#34;&gt;Sends emails on your behalf — useful for prior authorization letters, appeal correspondence, and patient communications. Only fires when you explicitly include a recipient email.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-example&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Send this prior authorization letter to auth@insurance.com&amp;#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;tool-badges&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;tool-badge&#34; style=&#34;background: #FF95001a; color: #FF9500;&#34;&gt;Communication&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;de-identification-example&#34;&gt;De-identification Example&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup&#34; style=&#34;margin: 2rem 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-avatar&#34;&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-title&#34;&gt;Chat&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;chat-mockup-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg user&#34;&gt;De-identify this note: &#34;John Smith, DOB 03/15/1958, MRN 12345678, presented to the ED on 01/20/2026 with chest pain.&#34;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;chat-msg assistant&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-avatar&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#10022;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;msg-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;p style=&#34;margin:0; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-on-dark);&#34;&gt;&#xA;          Here&#39;s the de-identified version:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;          &lt;span style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.15); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--primary-light);&#34;&gt;[Patient A]&lt;/span&gt;, DOB &lt;span style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.15); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--primary-light);&#34;&gt;[Date-1]&lt;/span&gt;, MRN &lt;span style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.15); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--primary-light);&#34;&gt;[ID-1]&lt;/span&gt;, presented to the ED on &lt;span style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.15); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--primary-light);&#34;&gt;[Date-2]&lt;/span&gt; with chest pain.&#xA;        &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
